        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 12:58AM CDT until June 8 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 145 AM CDT.

* At 1258 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Nara Visa,
moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northwestern Oldham and southwestern Hartley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
